---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'what-hearing-covers', text: 'What Hearing Coverage Includes', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'hearing-services', text: 'Hearing Services', level: 2 },
  { id: 'hearing-aids', text: 'Hearing Aid Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Vision Insurance', href: '/best/vision-insurance' },
  { title: 'Senior Insurance', href: '/best/senior-insurance' },
  { title: 'Chronic Condition Insurance', href: '/best/chronic-condition-insurance' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Premium Insurance', href: '/best/premium-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'hearingTests', header: 'Hearing Tests' },
  { key: 'hearingAids', header: 'Hearing Aids' },
  { key: 'cochlear', header: 'Cochlear Implants' },
  { key: 'limits', header: 'Coverage Limits' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', hearingTests: 'Yes', hearingAids: 'Partial', cochlear: 'Yes', limits: 'Varies by plan' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', hearingTests: 'Yes', hearingAids: 'Limited', cochlear: 'Yes', limits: '$2,000-5,000' },
  { provider: 'Aetna International', hearingTests: 'Yes', hearingAids: 'Some plans', cochlear: 'Yes', limits: 'Varies' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', hearingTests: 'Yes', hearingAids: 'Limited', cochlear: 'Some plans', limits: 'Low limits' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', hearingTests: 'Basic', hearingAids: 'No', cochlear: 'Limited', limits: 'Minimal' },
];

const servicesColumns = [
  { key: 'service', header: 'Service Type' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Typical Coverage' },
  { key: 'notes', header: 'Notes' },
];

const servicesRows = [
  { service: 'Hearing tests/audiometry', coverage: 'Usually covered', notes: 'Diagnostic testing' },
  { service: 'ENT consultations', coverage: 'Covered', notes: 'Specialist visits' },
  { service: 'Hearing aids', coverage: 'Limited coverage', notes: 'Often capped amounts' },
  { service: 'Cochlear implants', coverage: 'Often covered', notes: 'As medical procedure' },
  { service: 'Tinnitus treatment', coverage: 'Sometimes covered', notes: 'Varies by cause' },
  { service: 'Hearing rehabilitation', coverage: 'Some plans', notes: 'Post-implant therapy' },
  { service: 'Hearing aid batteries', coverage: 'Rarely covered', notes: 'Usually out-of-pocket' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Expat Insurance for Hearing Coverage 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance with hearing coverage. Find plans that cover hearing tests, hearing aids, cochlear implants, and ENT care abroad."
  headline="Best Expat Insurance for Hearing Coverage"
  subheadline="Hearing health matters. Here are the international health plans with the best coverage for hearing tests, hearing aids, cochlear implants, and audiology services."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-hearing-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for Hearing Coverage</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers offer the best hearing benefits:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">👂</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Hearing Coverage</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Comprehensive hearing coverage including tests, partial hearing aid benefits, and cochlear implant surgery.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🔊</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Cochlear Coverage</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Good cochlear implant coverage with hearing rehabilitation and defined hearing aid allowances.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🏥</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best US Audiology Access</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Aetna International</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Strong US audiology network with access to specialized hearing centers.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">⚠️</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Important Note</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Limited Coverage</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Hearing aids are often excluded or have low caps. Cochlear implants typically have better coverage as surgical procedures.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="what-hearing-covers">What Hearing Coverage Includes</h2>
  <p>
    Hearing coverage in international health insurance typically includes:
  </p>

  <h3>Diagnostic Services</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Audiometry (hearing tests)</li>
    <li>ENT specialist consultations</li>
    <li>Tympanometry and other ear tests</li>
    <li>Balance and vestibular testing</li>
    <li>Usually covered as standard outpatient care</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Medical Treatment</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Cochlear implant surgery</li>
    <li>Ear surgery (stapedectomy, etc.)</li>
    <li>Treatment for ear infections</li>
    <li>Tinnitus evaluation and treatment</li>
    <li>Covered as medically necessary procedures</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Hearing Devices</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Hearing aids (often limited or excluded)</li>
    <li>Cochlear implant devices</li>
    <li>Bone-anchored hearing systems</li>
    <li>Device programming and adjustment</li>
    <li>Usually subject to caps or limitations</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Protect Your Hearing Health"
    description="Compare plans with comprehensive hearing coverage."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Hearing Coverage Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Best Hearing Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers the most comprehensive hearing benefits among international insurers.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Hearing tests fully covered</li>
    <li>ENT consultations included</li>
    <li>Partial hearing aid benefits on some plans</li>
    <li>Cochlear implant surgery covered</li>
    <li>Post-implant rehabilitation</li>
    <li>Good network of audiology specialists</li>
    <li>Tinnitus treatment options</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing. Hearing aid coverage varies by plan tier. Best coverage on comprehensive plans. Worth reviewing specific limits for devices.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Good Cochlear Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers solid cochlear implant coverage with defined hearing benefits.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Cochlear implant surgery covered</li>
    <li>Hearing tests included</li>
    <li>Defined hearing aid allowances</li>
    <li>ENT specialist access</li>
    <li>Hearing rehabilitation coverage</li>
    <li>Good provider network</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Hearing aid limits apply (typically $2,000-5,000). Best coverage on premium plans. Good balance of coverage and cost.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Aetna International — US Audiology Access</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International provides good hearing coverage with strong US network.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to US audiology centers</li>
    <li>Hearing tests covered</li>
    <li>Cochlear implant coverage</li>
    <li>Some hearing aid benefits</li>
    <li>Good specialist network</li>
    <li>Care coordination available</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Best for those wanting US facility access. Hearing aid limits vary. Good overall hearing coverage on comprehensive plans.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/aetna-international">Read our full Aetna International review</a></p>

  <h2 id="hearing-services">Hearing Services Covered</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={servicesColumns} rows={servicesRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Hearing Tests</h3>
  <p>
    Diagnostic hearing services are typically covered:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Pure tone audiometry</li>
    <li>Speech audiometry</li>
    <li>Tympanometry</li>
    <li>Otoacoustic emissions testing</li>
    <li>Usually covered under outpatient benefits</li>
    <li>May require physician referral</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>ENT Care</h3>
  <p>
    Ear, nose, and throat specialist care:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Initial consultations</li>
    <li>Follow-up visits</li>
    <li>Treatment for ear conditions</li>
    <li>Pre-surgical evaluations</li>
    <li>Covered as specialist visits</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Surgical Procedures</h3>
  <p>
    Medically necessary ear surgeries:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Cochlear implant surgery</li>
    <li>Stapedectomy for otosclerosis</li>
    <li>Tympanoplasty (eardrum repair)</li>
    <li>Mastoidectomy</li>
    <li>Covered as inpatient procedures</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Comprehensive Hearing Care"
    description="Find plans that cover the hearing services you need."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="hearing-aids">Hearing Aid Coverage</h2>

  <h3>The Reality of Hearing Aid Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Hearing aids are one of the most limited benefits in international health insurance:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Many plans exclude hearing aids entirely</li>
    <li>Others have low caps ($1,000-5,000)</li>
    <li>Usually limited to every 3-5 years</li>
    <li>May only cover basic models</li>
    <li>Premium aids often exceed coverage limits</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Why Coverage Is Limited</h3>
  <p>
    Hearing aids are often considered:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Assistive devices rather than medical treatment</li>
    <li>Elective in many insurance frameworks</li>
    <li>High-cost items with frequent replacement needs</li>
    <li>Technology-driven with varying price points</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Cochlear Implants: Better Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Cochlear implants typically have better coverage because:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Classified as surgical procedures</li>
    <li>Medically necessary for severe hearing loss</li>
    <li>Covered under inpatient benefits</li>
    <li>Include device, surgery, and programming</li>
    <li>Post-implant rehabilitation often covered</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Tips for Hearing Aid Coverage</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Check specific policy language for hearing aids</li>
    <li>Ask about lifetime vs. annual limits</li>
    <li>Consider supplemental hearing benefits</li>
    <li>Compare local hearing aid costs to coverage</li>
    <li>Some countries have lower hearing aid costs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Are hearing aids covered by international health insurance?</h3>
  <p>
    Coverage varies significantly. Many plans exclude hearing aids or have low caps ($1,000-5,000). Premium plans may offer partial coverage. Always check specific policy language for hearing aid benefits and any replacement frequency limits.
  </p>

  <h3>Are cochlear implants covered?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, most comprehensive international health plans cover cochlear implant surgery as a medically necessary procedure. Coverage typically includes the surgery, device, and post-operative programming. Pre-authorization is usually required.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need a referral for hearing tests?</h3>
  <p>
    Depends on your plan. Some allow direct access to audiologists, others require physician or ENT referral. Diagnostic hearing tests are usually covered under outpatient benefits. Check your specific policy requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Is tinnitus treatment covered?</h3>
  <p>
    Treatment for tinnitus may be covered if there's an underlying medical cause. Evaluation and diagnosis are typically covered. Treatment options vary and coverage depends on the recommended approach and your specific plan.
  </p>

  <h3>How often can I get new hearing aids?</h3>
  <p>
    Plans with hearing aid coverage typically allow replacement every 3-5 years. Some have lifetime limits rather than periodic replacement. Coverage usually applies to one pair per benefit period. Check your specific policy terms.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I see any audiologist?</h3>
  <p>
    Most international health plans allow you to see any licensed audiologist, though some may have preferred providers. Out-of-network audiologists are usually still covered but may require claim submission. Verify coverage before your appointment.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Hearing coverage varies by plan and insurer. We are not insurance brokers or medical professionals. Always verify current coverage directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
